This paper discusses the design of a cognitive dynamic network architecture (CDNA) for efficient sharing of network resources and service delivery. The paper focuses on policies for data and spectrum trading, which are key components of network resource sharing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and policies for efficient resource allocation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the importance of trustworthiness in the collaborative network, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
